A question a lot of Googlers
have been pinging me with

01:00:00.850 --> 01:00:05.450
is how does a Bay Area
SUI software engineer end

01:00:05.450 --> 01:00:07.580
up going to UC Santa
Cruz to study journalism

01:00:07.580 --> 01:00:09.251
and becoming a journalist?

01:00:09.251 --> 01:00:11.750
ANIL ANANTHASWAMY: It was just
a 90-mile trip down the road.

01:00:14.410 --> 01:00:17.920
No, seriously, it
was around, I think,

01:00:17.920 --> 01:00:21.310
I was in Berkeley building
network management systems.

01:00:21.310 --> 01:00:23.220
In fact, I have a
colleague from that company

01:00:23.220 --> 01:00:24.446
who was here at Google.

01:00:24.446 --> 01:00:25.320
I don't see him here.

01:00:28.470 --> 01:00:32.130
I think four or five
years into my software job

01:00:32.130 --> 01:00:36.070
in Berkeley I really began
to feel the desire to write.

01:00:36.070 --> 01:00:37.800
And I thought I would
be writing fiction.

01:00:37.800 --> 01:00:39.716
And so I would take a
few months off each year

01:00:39.716 --> 01:00:42.455
and try my hand at fiction.

01:00:42.455 --> 01:00:43.830
And then somebody
told me what do

01:00:43.830 --> 01:00:47.240
you UC Santa Cruz program,
which is science communication

01:00:47.240 --> 01:00:49.000
program-- science
writing program.

01:00:49.000 --> 01:00:54.780
And that was a really key moment
because I really love science.

01:00:54.780 --> 01:00:56.000
And I love reading about it.

01:00:56.000 --> 01:00:59.130
And it never occurred to me that
it is something I could write.

01:00:59.130 --> 01:01:01.590
So when I found out
about the program,

01:01:01.590 --> 01:01:02.950
I said, OK, it's just one year.

01:01:02.950 --> 01:01:05.030
How long can I go?

01:01:05.030 --> 01:01:07.790
So I went and did the program.

01:01:07.790 --> 01:01:10.670
The program led to an internship
with "New Scientist" in London.

01:01:10.670 --> 01:01:13.690
So I went to London
for six months.

01:01:13.690 --> 01:01:15.180
And I was still
wondering whether I

01:01:15.180 --> 01:01:18.230
could earn a living doing
writing So I came back.

01:01:18.230 --> 01:01:21.880
And for the first year,
maybe about 10 months,

01:01:21.880 --> 01:01:24.880
I did double duty about
three and a half days

01:01:24.880 --> 01:01:28.300
of writing more code and
then three and a half days

01:01:28.300 --> 01:01:32.250
of writing not code,
but journalism.

01:01:32.250 --> 01:01:34.540
And then 10 months
into it, I realized

01:01:34.540 --> 01:01:36.144
I could pay my
bills with writing.

